1. *responsive is fluid and adapts to the size of the screen no matter what the target device.
*Adaptive design uses static layouts based on breakpoints which don't respond once they're initially loaded.

2. mobile first means to design from mobile size then expand to larger setting. desktop first means content is disigned for larger area and adjustments are made for smaller screens.

